Fourth Department,

June, 1938.

(June 28, 1938.) Joseph J. Lunghino, Appellant, v. The Marine Trust Company of Buffalo and Others, Respondents.

Order affirmed, with ten dollars costs and disbursements. All concur. (The order denies plaintiff’s motion to vacate a default judgment in an action for malicious prosecution.) Present — Crosby, Lewis, Cunningham, Taylor and Dowling, JJ.
